"```sql\nSELECT \n  (COUNT(DISTINCT fd.id) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT c.id)) AS percentage\nFROM \n  cards c\nJOIN \n  foreign_data fd ON c.uuid = fd.uuid\nWHERE \n  fd.language = 'Chinese Simplified';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of cards available in Chinese Simplified by joining the `cards` and `foreign_data` tables on their `uuid` columns, filtering for rows where the language is 'Chinese Simplified', and then computing the percentage based on the count of distinct card IDs."